### Section 2: System and Assessment Overview

**System Description:** MyClinic OpenMRS is a cloud-hosted electronic health record system deployed on Amazon Web Services supporting clinical operations for MyClinic. The system processes, stores, and transmits electronic protected health information (ePHI) including clinical encounter documentation, medication records, laboratory results, and patient demographic data. The system serves clinical staff, administrative staff, and the ISSO and IT Administrator who operate and maintain the system.

**Authorization Boundary:** The authorization boundary encompasses the EC2 application server, RDS database instance, S3 backup storage, and the AWS account configuration (IAM, CloudTrail, GuardDuty, Config, Security Hub, KMS) supporting the OpenMRS deployment. AWS physical infrastructure controls are addressed through inheritance of AWS SOC 2 certification.

**Security Categorization:** SC OpenMRS = {(confidentiality, HIGH), (integrity, HIGH), (availability, HIGH)} — Overall: HIGH. The High categorization reflects the ePHI content of the system, the use of OpenMRS for real-time clinical decision support, and the absence of a tested paper-based downtime procedure.

**Assessment Scope:** Full High baseline assessment per SAP dated [date]. All control families in the tailored High baseline were assessed. Scoped-out controls (PE family, core OpenMRS development SA controls, physical media controls) were verified as appropriately documented in the SSP.

**Assessment Methods:** NIST SP 800-53A examine, interview, and test methods applied throughout. Technical testing conducted in the production AWS environment (read-only) and OpenMRS test environment (application-level testing with synthetic data). Interviews conducted with ISSO, IT Administrator, Health IT Manager, and Compliance Officer.

**Assessment Limitations:** The following assessment activities were not fully executable within the assessment scope and timeline:
- Full penetration testing of the OpenMRS application (out of scope per SAP rules of engagement — discovery only)
- Assessment of Laboratory Information System security controls (out of boundary — addressed via BAA and ISA review)
- Validation of alternate processing site failover (CP-7 — the alternate site arrangement exists but failover testing has not been conducted; this is an open POA&M item)

