#### Finding A-7: IAM Entity Creation Not Listed as ISSO-Notification Change Management Trigger

**Control:** CM-3 (Configuration Change Control)

**Severity:** Moderate

**Finding Status:** New finding — root cause of Finding A-3

**Description:** The change management procedure (CM-3) lists security-relevant change categories requiring ISSO notification — including security group modifications, IAM policy changes, and encryption configuration changes. The procedure does not explicitly list the creation of new IAM entities (users, roles, service accounts) as a required notification category. This omission allowed the creation of the service account identified in Finding A-3 to proceed without ISSO awareness, preventing the account from being included in the IAM inventory and quarterly review scope.

Findings A-3 and A-7 share the same root cause. Remediating A-3 (correcting the service account configuration) without remediating A-7 (updating the change management trigger list) leaves the organization exposed to the same pattern recurring — a future IAM entity created without ISSO notification would again miss the quarterly review process.

**Evidence:** CM-3 procedure document reviewed [date]; IT Administrator interview [date] confirming IAM entity creation was not recognized as a security-relevant change requiring ISSO notification; A-3 finding circumstances.

**Risk:** Moderate. The systemic process gap elevates risk beyond the individual instance of Finding A-3 — it represents a category of blind spots in the IAM governance program.

**Remediation Recommendation:** Add IAM entity creation (new IAM users, roles, groups, and service accounts) to the CM-3 ISSO notification trigger list. Brief the IT Administrator on the updated procedure. Consider implementing an automated notification: AWS EventBridge rule triggering an SNS notification to the ISSO on `iam:CreateUser`, `iam:CreateRole`, and `iam:CreateGroup` API calls — providing automated notification that supplements the procedural requirement.

**POA&M Required:** Yes. Target completion: 30 days from authorization.

